## Working here

- Validation: `{{VALIDATION_CMD}}`
- Pre-commit linter: ERROR blocks, WARN advises (`tools/lint.py`). Arm once on a fresh
  clone: `git config core.hooksPath .githooks`.
- **Never codify silently.** Rule and convention changes are proposed and accepted
  before writing — use `/codify`.
- **Design calls leave a record.** Project-internal design decisions land as
  date-slug files in `docs/decisions/` — the call plus its why — so a later session
  inherits the reasoning instead of relitigating it. Cross-cutting calls that outlive
  the project go to your portfolio-level decision store.
- Wrapping up mid-task: `/handoff` writes a decision-ready handoff to `handoffs/`.

## Intake guard

When a build request is material-shaped ("extract / consolidate / clean up X") but names
no moment of use, stop before building and get the **day-one user story** ("when I do X,
Y happens") and the **anti-goal** (what it must NOT be). Material-shaped asks default to
docs-about-the-thing instead of the thing; for multi-session builds, offer `/grill-me`.

## Engineering defaults

Language-agnostic; this project's own conventions override. Fail loud, not silently —
surface unexpected state; keep error handling narrow and put diagnostic context in the
message; use enums/constants for bounded value sets; names should communicate purpose;
extract for clarity but don't abstract ahead of real reuse.

## Execution discipline

- **Disagreement and pushback**: never silently execute an approach believed to be
  mistaken. Raise concerns at planning time, calibrated by consequence: a preference →
  note in one sentence and proceed; likely rework or hard-to-reverse choice → stop and
  ask; confident the approach breaks something → don't execute, explain and propose an
  alternative.
- **Effort–expectation mismatch**: when a task proves disproportionately hard relative to
  what the user seems to expect, stop and surface the discrepancy rather than pushing
  through. The likely cause is a broken premise. Realign first.
- **After two failed attempts**: stop and diagnose the root cause before trying a third —
  don't rerun unchanged commands or iterate patch variations. Present the fix and name
  whether it addresses the root cause or only a symptom.
- **Review before committing**: when a durable chunk is done, review it end-to-end before
  committing. Run a test or linter when its result changes your next step — not as a
  reflex.
- **Verify load-bearing claims**: a "shared / reused / same-as / subset / core" statement
  is true only if the call graph makes it so — verify structurally, never nominally.

## Subagent discipline

For non-trivial Agent tool calls (research, multi-step investigation, design work), end
the prompt with: "End your response with a `## Takeaways` block: decisions made, gotchas
hit, lessons worth keeping." Subagent transcripts are not visible to the main session —
only the return value is — so without this, reasoning that surfaced lessons is lost.

## Communication

- **Context before questions**: before asking the user to decide anything that rests on
  context they haven't seen, present that context and end the turn; ask in a following turn.
- **Concision**: surface what the reader needs to act on or understand; cut the rest.
- **Visibility during a long stretch**: before going heads-down, post a one-line "here's
  what I'm about to do," then surface findings-oriented status at each checkpoint. "Found
  X, which points to Y, so I'm now checking Z" signals; "Reading file X" does not.
- **Technology currency**: for questions about current best-in-class tools, models, or
  libraries, run a web research call before recommending — training data may be a year or
  more stale.
- **Don't write predictably stale content**: when a statement tracks a moving target
  (versions, prices, counts), point at the source of truth or leave it out.

## Context routing

In a repo with context-management machinery (`docs/decisions/`, `/handoff`,
`/wrap-session`, `/codify`), durable knowledge goes to that machinery rather than harness
auto-memory. Route by shape: in-flight resumable context → `/handoff`; findable session
history → `/wrap-session`; rule or convention → `/codify`; design call plus its why →
`docs/decisions/`. In a bare repo with none of this machinery, harness auto-memory is the
right home.

